🏏 Porralia Batting App — Project Overview
This is a Node.js/Express backend for a prediction-based betting/gaming platform (called "batting" — likely a phonetic spelling of "betting" in the regional context).
What it does:
Core Concept: Users join prediction pools, pay points to enter, make predictions on questions/outcomes, and earn rewards based on whether they're correct.
Key Features:
User System

Register, login, OTP verification via email
JWT-based authentication with token blacklisting (logout support)
Profile photo uploads via Cloudinary
Invite link system to bring in new users
Monthly rewards for active users

Pool / Prediction System

Admins/users create "pools" with a question and multiple options
Other users join by spending points
Each participant submits a prediction
Pool has two reward systems: Points Awards or Podium (winner/runner-up/second runner-up)
Results are declared, winners are calculated, points distributed automatically
Leaderboard tracking per pool

Notifications

Firebase push notifications sent to users
Email notifications via SendGrid/Nodemailer

Categories

Pools are organized into categories (sports, cricket, etc.)

Tech Stack:
LayerTechnologyRuntimeNode.jsFrameworkExpress.jsDatabaseMongoDB (via Mongoose)AuthJWT + bcryptFile StorageCloudinaryEmailsSendGrid + NodemailerPush NotificationsFirebase AdminSchedulingnode-cron (monthly rewards)
In short:
It's the backend API for a fantasy/prediction gaming app — users pay entry points, predict outcomes of events (likely cricket matches given the name), and win points/rewards based on accuracy.
